iterature, and over a period of three months she observed and documented differences between alternative and traditional schools. In trying to reconcile the gap between those systems, Morrison details the lessons she learned about teachers, students, curriculum, and the entire conception of why we educate our children.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aEducationxAims and objectiveszUnited States. 0aFree schoolszUnited States. 0aSchool management and organizationzUnited States. 4aEducation : Foundations of Education. 7aEDUCATION / Philosophy, Theory & Social Aspects.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791479872423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791479872/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles